that often comes at the expense of keeping children in school.\r\n','FeatureImages/family suport.jpg',0,'2018-01-19 14:34:52'),(37,5,'1. Introduction','Education is the process of the teaching and training of the child. It is about imparting skills and the acquisition of knowledge for a particular trade or profession in which appropriate methods are applied This means that the focus is on learning which strengthens the capacities of children to act progressively on their own behalf through the acquisition of relevant knowledge, useful skills and appropriate attitudes; and which creates for children, and helps them create for themselves and others, places of safety, security and healthy interaction.\r\n','FeatureImages/introduction.jpg',0,'2018-01-19 12:46:23'),(38,0,'2. Education and development','Education plays a huge role in development and economic growth, and consequently, in combating poverty. The education was valued by employers not because of the cognitive skills. Education is the  judged to be responsible for reproducing the social hierarchies in society in a stable and predictable way.\r\neducation or training raises the productivity of employees by imparting valuable\r\nknowledge and skills. Thus, it raises workerÃ¢Â€Â™s future lifetime earnings increment.\r\n','FeatureImages/development.jpg',0,'2018-01-19 13:24:36'),(42,0,'4. Peace education.','Peace education seeks to help students gain the ability to prevent conflict, and to resolve conflict peacefully when it does arise, whether on the intrapersonal, interpersonal,intergroup, national or international level. Peace education addresses cognitive, affective and behavioural learning and can occur both within schools, through curriculum development and teacher education, and outside of schools, through camps, sports.\r\n','FeatureImages/peaceeducation.png',0,'2018-01-19 14:36:59'),(43,0,'5. Good health and nutrition.','Physically and psychosocially healthy children learn well.Adequate nutrition is critica