ctual and forecasted water shortages are not limited to developing countries. In developed countries shortages are being felt through restrictions on waterÃ¢Â€Â™s use.\r\n','FeatureImages/introduction.jpg',0,'2018-01-19 19:06:49'),(72,12,'2. Tips to promote water conservation in households','A. In the kitchen:\r\n \r\nCollect unused water in a bucket and use it afterwards to mop the floor or water plants.\r\nWash vegetables and fruits in a bowl, not under tap.\r\nSelect one glass (or one bottle) for the day, you will reduce the number of glasses to be washed.\r\nWhen washing dishes by hand, fill one basin with soapy water and one with rinse water, do not use running water.\r\nDonÃ¢Â€Â™t rinse dishes before loading dishwasher.\r\nWhen buying a new dishwasher, consider purchasing a water-saving model.\r\n \r\n','FeatureImages/kitchen.jpg',0,'2018-01-19 19:11:11'),(73,0,'B. In the bathroom','Use a mug to rinse your razor, not running water.\r\nTurn off running water while brushing your teeth or shampooing.\r\nTake shorter showers or, if you take a bath, fill the tub only 1/3 full.\r\nInstall tap aerators and water-saving showerheads.\r\nSave water every time you flush the toilet by placing a bottle filled with pebbles in the toilet tank (to reduce its volume) and/or reduce the number of flushes.\r\nPut food colouring in your toilet tank: if it seeps into the toilet bowl within 30 minutes (without flushing) there is a leak and you have to fix it.\r\n \r\n','FeatureImages/washroom.jpg',0,'2018-01-19 19:13:39'),(74,0,'C. In the laundry room','Wash laundry only when the machine is full.\r\nIf you have a top-loader washing machine and you need to replace it, get a front-loader one (it requires less water per cycle).\r\nDonÃ¢Â€Â™t use running water while hand-washing clothes.\r\nRecycle clothes-washing water for mopping the floor or flushing the toilet.\r\n','FeatureImages/laundry.jpg',0,'2018-01-19 19:15:20'),(75,0,'D. Outside the house:','If you really have to, do wash your car or motorbike with a bucket of water, not a running hose.\r\nUse a broom, not a hose, to clean driveways and sidewalks.\r\nInstall a shut-off nozzle on your hose.\r\nPlant your garden with drought-resistant native plants (they retain water and help reduce runoff).\r\nWater plants only in the early morning or the evening and avoid doing it when it is windy to reduce loss to evaporation.\r\n','FeatureImages/outside.jpg',0,'2018-01-19 19:17:15'),(76,0,'D. Everywhere ','Stop dripping taps by turning them off completely (but not so tightly that you damage the valve seats) and if they are still dripping repair them.\r\n','FeatureImages/every.jpg',0,'2018-01-19 19:20:39'),(77,0,'3. Why is it important to save water ?','The current average consumption of water worldwide is estimated around 1,700 LPCD, 69% of which is used for agricultural purposes. In the year 2000 consumption was double than in 1960. Such trend is no longer sustainable and without conservation efforts this vital supply of water may be exhausted. \r\nEveryone needs not only drinking but also eating and the worldÃ¢Â€Â™s population growth has led to an increase in the demand for irrigation to grow food crops. Conservation helps offset the inevitable reduction of our individual quota.\r\nThe majority of life on Earth is tied to the supply of water, and overuse of water threatened habitats of fish and other life forms which help sustain us.Conservation protects the balance of life on Earth, which would be upset by a reduction in the water supply. \r\n\r\n\r\n Remember: water is not processed and delivered to your house for free, whenever you save water you also save money! \r\n','FeatureImages/conclusion.jpg',0,'2018-01-19 19:23:19'),(78,12,' B. In the bathroom:','Use a mug to rinse your razor, not running water.\r\nTurn off running water while brushing your teeth or shampooing.\r\nTake shorter showers or, if you take a bath, fill the tub only 1/3 full.\r\nInstall tap aerators and water-saving showerheads.