ape poverty. In particular, the sons of educated mothers in rural areas were 27% more likely to find off-farm employment.\r\n','FeatureImages/canva-photo-editor (8).png',0,'2018-01-29 12:42:34'),(115,31,'9. MothersÃ¢Â€Â™ education has saved millions of childrenÃ¢Â€Â™s Lives.','Between 1990 and 2012, the number of deaths of children under 5 fell from 12.6 to 6.6 million, of which 6.1 million were in low and lower middle income\r\ncountries. Maternal education accounts for half of all lives saved through lower child mortality rates, while economic growth accounts for less than a tenth. To\r\neliminate preventable child deaths urgent action is needed, and education must be part of it. If all women in low and lower middle income countries completed secondary education, the under-5 mortality rate would\r\nfall by 49% an annual saving of 3 million lives.\r\n\r\n','FeatureImages/Defining Quality in Education.jpg',0,'2018-01-29 12:55:28'),(116,31,'10. Education Helps Good Economic Growth. ','Education is a prerequisite for short and long-term economic growth: No country has achieved continuous and rapid economic growth without at least 40 percent of adults being able to read and write.\r\n\r\n Failing to offer girls the same educational opportunity as boys costs developing countries $92 billion each year, according to a study by Plan International. That\'s $1 trillion per decade in forgone earnings and unnecessary costs. \r\n A personÃ¢Â€Â™s earnings increase by 10 percent for each year of schooling they receive, translating to one percent annual increase in GDP if good quality education is offered to the entire population.\r\nÃ¢Â€ÂœEducating GirlsÃ¢Â€Â yields a higher rate of return than any other investment available in the developing world.\r\n','FeatureImages/economic growth.png',0,'2018-01-29 12:58:15'),(117,31,'11. Water and  Energy Sustainability.','By increasing awareness and concern, education can encourage people to reduce their impact on the environment by taking action such as using energy and water more efficiently.\r\n\r\nSuch behaviour becomes increasingly important as people in high income countries are called upon to modify their consumption and take other measures that limit environmental harm.\r\n\r\n','FeatureImages/canva-photo-editor (10).png',0,'2018-01-29 13:06:14'),(118,31,'12.  Good Jobs.','Much of the benefit of higher education accrues to individual students and their families. For members of all demographic groups, average earnings increase measurably with higher levels of education. Over their working lives, typical college graduates earn about 73 percent more than typical high school graduates, and those with advanced degrees earn two to three times as much as high school graduates. More educated people are less likely to be unemployed and less likely to live in poverty.\r\n','FeatureImages/goodjobs.png',0,'2018-01-29 13:09:58'),(119,31,'13. Conclusion.','Education can accelerate progress towards the achievement of each of the proposed sustainable development goals for 2018 and beyond in a multiplicity of ways. Not only is education a basic human right but, it is vital for development. Education enables individuals, especially women, to live and aspire to healthy, meaningful, creative and resilient lives. \r\n','FeatureImages/canva-photo-editor (12).png',0,'2018-01-29 13:14:05'),(121,31,'New','ANBVC','FeatureImages/index.jpeg',1,'2018-02-10 16:45:59'),(123,38,'My Book','If ur add new book then plz send me the msg ','FeatureImages/Dora_A.jpg',0,'2018-02-12 14:10:02'),(124,41,'What is a carbon footprint?','The term carbon footprint is commonly used to describe  total amount of CO2 and other greenhouse gas','FeatureImages/what is.jpeg',0,'2018-02-19 19:29:49'),(125,41,'Decrease your carbon footprint.','Everyone  start to save the climate by decreasing the own carbon footprint which means to reduce it.','FeatureImages/own role.png',0,'2018-02-19 19:31:31'),(126,41,'@Important of Electrical Devices','The foll